---
By: Heraclitus
Source:
  ID: 996c9a12-d13d-4597-a783-506d70cd1736
Verse: 112
Translator: Charles Kahn
Book: Anaximander and the Origins of Greek Cosmology
Publisher: Hackett Publishing
Copyright: 1994
---
Thinking well is the greatest excellence; and wisdom is to act and
speak what is true, perceiving things according to their nature.
